{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850518523,"sessionID":"ses_2870fb728ffemxuYhZ8NJsku03","part":{"id":"prt_d78f0737e001ApfMo25Kv8vzco","messageID":"msg_d78f061aa001T1dxIFNXO5GSgp","sessionID":"ses_2870fb728ffemxuYhZ8NJsku03","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_999b76fc508e4ad1b851d079","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Attribute | Value |\n6: |-----------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-012 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: \n12: ## Related Components\n13: \n14: The session store integrates with the Kubernetes client library (`client-go`) which provides typed clients for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. The client-go library supports `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs for sandbox orchestration. Session metadata may reference these K8s resources via the `runtime.agentcube` clientset.\n15: \n16: See `deployment/client-go.md` for full client-go library specification.\n17: \n18: ## Module\n19: \n20: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n21: \n22: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n23: \n24: ### Store interface (exact signatures)\n25: \n26: ```go\n27: package store\n28: \n29: import (\n30:     \"context\"\n31:     \"time\"\n32: \n33:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n34: )\n35: \n36: type Store interface {\n37:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n38:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n39:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n40:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n41:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n42:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n43:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n44:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n45:     Close() error\n46: }\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Errors\n50: \n51: ```go\n52: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ### Provider type constants (`singleton.go`)\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: const (\n59:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n60:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n61: )\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Singleton\n65: \n66: ```go\n67: var (\n68:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n69:     provider      Store\n70: )\n71: \n72: func Storage() Store\n73: func initStore() error\n74: ```\n75: \n76: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n77: \n78: ### Sandbox document type\n79: \n80: Stored JSON unmarshals to `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n81: \n82: ```go\n83: type SandboxInfo struct {\n84:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n85:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n86:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n87:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n88:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n89:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n90:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n91:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n92:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n93: }\n94: \n95: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n96:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n97:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n98:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n99: }\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ## Redis implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n103: \n104: ### Struct\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: type redisStore struct {\n108:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n109:     sessionPrefix        string\n110:     expiryIndexKey       string\n111:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Fixed key patterns\n116: \n117: | Field | Value |\n118: |-------|--------|\n119: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n120: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n121: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n122: \n123: ### Connection options (`makeRedisOptions`)\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: return &redisv9.Options{\n127:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // REDIS_ADDR\n128:     Password: redisPassword, // REDIS_PASSWORD\n129: }, nil\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Environment variables (Redis)\n133: \n134: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n135: |----------|----------|--------|\n136: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | |\n137: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n138: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default `redis` |\n139: \n140: ### Operations summary\n141: \n142: | Method | Redis commands |\n143: |--------|----------------|\n144: | `Ping` | `PING` → expect `PONG` |\n145: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n146: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n147: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n148: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n149: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n150: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n151: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n152: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n153: \n154: - `List*` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`.\n155: - `sessionKey(id)` → `sessionPrefix + sessionID`.\n156: \n157: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n158: \n159: ### Struct\n160: \n161: ```go\n162: type valkeyStore struct {\n163:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n164:     sessionPrefix        string\n165:     expiryIndexKey       string\n166:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: Same string constants as Redis for prefix and ZSET keys.\n171: \n172: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n173: \n174: ```go\n175: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n176:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n177:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: Optional: `DisableCache` from `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, must be true); `ForceSingleClient` from `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, must be true).\n182: \n183: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n184: \n185: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n186: |----------|----------|--------|\n187: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list → `InitAddress` |\n188: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n189: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n190: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n191: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n192: \n193: ### Operations summary\n194: \n195: | Method | Valkey API |\n196: |--------|------------|\n197: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n198: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n199: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n200: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n201: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n202: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n203: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n204: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n205: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n206: \n207: ### ZSET score semantics\n208: \n209: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store.\n210: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`; `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n211: \n212: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n213: \n214: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` builds all `session:{id}` keys and uses single `Mget`; comment states keys should be in same slot (deployment consideration).\n215: \n216: ## Dependencies (store package imports)\n217: \n218: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n219: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n220: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n221: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n222: \n223: ## Architecture\n224: \n225: ### Overview\n226: \n227: The Session Store module provides a unified interface for persisting sandbox metadata with support for both Redis and Valkey backends. The design follows the provider pattern, allowing runtime selection of the underlying storage backend through configuration.\n228: \n229: ```\n230: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n231: │                    pkg/store                            │\n232: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n233: │  ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐  │\n234: │  │   Store     │    │ redisStore  │    │ valkeyStore │  │\n235: │  │  Interface  │◄───│  (Redis 9)  │    │ (Valkey)    │  │\n236: │  └─────────────┘    └─────────────┘    └─────────────┘  │\n237: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n238: │  Singleton: Storage() → Store                           │\n239: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n240: │  Data Model: Session ID → SandboxInfo (JSON)           │\n241: │  Index 1: session:expiry (ZSET) → sessionID:expireTS   │\n242: │  Index 2: session:last_activity (ZSET) → sessionID:ts  │\n243: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Data Flow\n247: \n248: 1. **Store Operations**: All write operations update both the session document and the two ZSET indexes atomically via pipeline/multi commands.\n249: 2. **List Operations**: Query ZSET for session IDs, then batch-fetch documents.\n250: 3. **GC Operations**: ListExpiredSandboxes and ListInactiveSandboxes support garbage collection of stale sessions.\n251: \n252: ## Error Handling\n253: \n254: ### Error Types\n255: \n256: | Error | Condition | Return Value |\n257: |-------|-----------|--------------|\n258: | `ErrNotFound` | Session key missing | `errors.New(\"store: not found\")` |\n259: | Validation errors | Nil sandbox, zero ExpiresAt | Context-specific messages |\n260: | Connection errors | Redis/Valkey unreachable | Propagated from client |\n261: \n262: ### Error Recovery\n263: \n264: - **Get operations**: Return `ErrNotFound` for missing keys, propagate other errors.\n265: - **Write operations**: Pipeline failures abort the entire operation; partial writes do not occur.\n266: - **List operations**: Tolerate missing document keys for orphaned ZSET members.\n267: \n268: ### Logging\n269: \n270: - Initialization failures log via `klog.Fatalf`.\n271: - Valkey optional flags logged at info level during option building.\n272: \n273: ## Testing Strategy\n274: \n275: ### Unit Tests\n276: \n277: | File | Coverage |\n278: |------|----------|\n279: | `store_redis_test.go` | Redis store implementation |\n280: | `store_valkey_test.go` | Valkey store implementation |\n281: | `singleton_test.go` | Singleton initialization |\n282: \n283: ### Test Approach\n284: \n285: - **Mock strategy**: Use interfaces for Redis/Valkey clients to enable mock-based testing.\n286: - **Test fixtures**: Predefined `SandboxInfo` objects for CRUD test cases.\n287: - **Integration tests**: Point to test Redis/Valkey instances via environment variables.\n288: \n289: ### Key Test Scenarios\n290: \n291: 1. **Ping**: Verify connectivity returns PONG.\n292: 2. **CRUD cycle**: Store → Get → Update → Delete.\n293: 3. **Not found**: Get/Update/Delete on missing session returns `ErrNotFound`.\n294: 4. **List queries**: Verify ZSET-based listing returns correct sessions.\n295: 5. **Atomicity**: Pipeline failures leave no partial state.\n296: 6. **Singleton**: Concurrent Storage() calls initialize exactly once.\n297: \n298: ## File Structure\n299: \n300: ```\n301: pkg/store/\n302: ├── design.md           # This file\n303: ├── singleton.go        # Storage(), initStore()\n304: ├── store.go            # Store interface definition\n305: ├── errors.go           # ErrNotFound definition\n306: ├── store_redis.go      # Redis implementation\n307: ├── store_valkey.go     # Valkey implementation\n308: ├── store_redis_test.go # Redis tests\n309: ├── store_valkey_test.go# Valkey tests\n310: └── singleton_test.go   # Singleton tests\n311: ```\n\n(End of file - total 311 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store — Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| AR | AR-012 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n\n## Related Components\n\nThe session store integrates with the Kubernetes client library (`client-go`) which provides typed clients for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group. The client-go library supports `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs for sandbox orchestration. Session metadata may reference these K8s resources via the `runtime.agentcube` clientset.\n\nSee `deployment/client-go.md` for full client-go library specification.\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/session-store/design.md","time":{"start":1775850518494,"end":1775850518520}}}}
