{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850525489,"sessionID":"ses_2870fb728ffemxuYhZ8NJsku03","part":{"id":"prt_d78f08b68001cYcjFGNX4nhFFV","messageID":"msg_d78f07849001VMkOeEEthkkB4r","sessionID":"ses_2870fb728ffemxuYhZ8NJsku03","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_78f36c247d46461e857c9b06","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-012\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/store`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: - **Base Specs**: \n14:   - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n15:   - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Store interface\n16:   - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Background\n21: \n22: The agentcube system requires a session storage abstraction to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id. The store module provides a unified interface over Redis and Valkey backends, with support for:\n23: - Session CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete)\n24: - Expiry-based and activity-based session listing for garbage collection\n25: - Index maintenance via sorted sets\n26: - Provider selection via environment variables\n27: - Singleton initialization pattern\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n32: \n33: ### Scenario: Store interface provides all required methods\n34: \n35: **GIVEN** a configured Redis or Valkey backend  \n36: **WHEN** the `Store` interface is used  \n37: **THEN** the following methods are available:\n38: - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` — verifies connectivity\n39: - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — retrieves sandbox by session id\n40: - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` — creates new sandbox record\n41: - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` — updates existing sandbox\n42: - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error` — removes sandbox\n43: - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — lists expired sessions\n44: - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — lists inactive sessions\n45: - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` — updates last activity timestamp\n46: - `Close() error` — closes the store connection\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Requirement: Provider Selection\n51: \n52: ### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Redis provider\n53: \n54: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"redis\"` (case-insensitive)  \n55: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n56: **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed using environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n57: \n58: ### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Valkey provider\n59: \n60: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"` (case-insensitive)  \n61: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n62: **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed using environment variables `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n63: \n64: ### Scenario: Default provider is Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n65: \n66: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set  \n67: **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes  \n68: **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed by default\n69: \n70: ### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n71: \n72: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to an unsupported value (e.g., `\"memcached\"`)  \n73: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n74: **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n79: \n80: ### Scenario: Redis requires REDIS_ADDR\n81: \n82: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `redis` or unset  \n83: **WHEN** Redis store initializes without `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable  \n84: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating REDIS_ADDR is required\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n89: **WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n90: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n91: \n92: ### Scenario: Redis password optional when explicitly disabled\n93: \n94: **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set  \n95: **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n96: **WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty  \n97: **THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 397. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-012\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Specs**: \n  - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n  - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Store interface\n  - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n\n---\n\n## Background","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775850525462,"end":1775850525486}}}}
